column5: Hey! Does anyone know a good site to buy tackle,gear etc online?  Thanks!

Pro Tackle in Belleville is a good place to deal with depending on what your looking for.  https://www.google.ca/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=1&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=0CB4QFjAA&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.protacklemuskyshop.com%2F&ei=aLUWVcakFc-fyATw2IHQDQ&usg=AFQjCNGOGj_9Rq9Z0hihOtRU7orhQdfTxg
I started dealing with these guys last year and find their service is excellent and their prices fair.  http://www.luremaking.com/
It really depends what your looking to buy, but the two sites mentioned above are both great. I use protackle for lots of gear, and lure making for my worm harness supplies.  S.
Overstock Bait always has killer deals, I use them all the time.  http://www.overstockbait.com/
the classifieds right here on OFC
http://www.gagnonsports.com/index.php http://www.cabelas.com (I never order from the Canadian site) http://www.yourbobbersdown.com/ http://www.jamminjigs.com/ http://www.americanlegacyfishing.com/
For tackle in Canada it's hard to beat pro tackle musky shop. They do have everything plus shipping is free on orders over $150

I started dealing with these guys last year and find their service is excellent and their prices fair.  http://www.luremaking.com/   Are they from Canada?  When ordering from the US, are you guys getting charges with customs?
